subaward_description: THE ENDPOINT SECURITY DIVISION (ID3) PROVIDES THE ENTERPRISE-LEVEL SERVICES TO ENABLE AUTOMATED CONFIGURATION ASSESSMENT, REMEDIATION, AND REPORTING. THE ENDPOINT SECURITY DIVISION PROVIDES SOLUTIONS TO PROTECT WARFIGHTER MISSIONS THROUGH THE DELIVERY OF AUTOMATED DATA SHARING CAPABILITIES. ENDPOINT SECURITY IS THE INTEGRATION OF ENTERPRISE IA APPLICATIONS, TOOLS, AND DATA STANDARDS TO SUPPORT AUTOMATED PROCESSES FOR RISK MANAGEMENT, DATA EXPOSURE, AND DELIVERY TO BIG DATA STORAGE. SOLUTIONS PROVIDE FUNCTIONALITY TO PERFORM: DISCOVERY AND MANAGEMENT OF ASSETS USING STANDARDIZED AUTOMATED TOOLS; COMPLIANCE CHECKING OF ASSETS; ALLOW FOR THE REMEDIATION OF NON-SECURE CONFIGURATIONS; CREATE AND DISTRIBUTE CONTENT FOR VULNERABILITY AND CONFIGURATION TOOLS; AND DELIVERY OF ACTIONABLE RESULTS TO IMPROVE DOD SECURITY READINESS/AWARENESS.

ENDPOINT SECURITY IS THE INTEGRATION OF ENTERPRISE IA APPLICATIONS, TOOLS, AND DATA STANDARDS TO SUPPORT AUTOMATED PROCESSES FOR RISK MANAGEMENT, DATA EXPOSURE, AND DELIVERY TO BIG DATA STORAGE. THE OPERATIONAL EVALUATION CELL (OEC) IS THE SUPPORT ELEMENT WITHIN THE JITC OPERATIONAL TEST AND EVALUATION (OT&E) DIVISION RESPONSIBLE FOR ESTABLISHING AND MAINTAINING THE COMMANDS OT&E POLICIES AND PROCEDURES, AND FOR PROVIDING TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE AND TRAINING TO JITC TEST TEAMS CONDUCTING OT&E. THE OEC MAINTAINS THE JITC OT&E GUIDEBOOK, THE OFFICIAL SOURCE FOR INFORMATION GUIDING JITC TEST TEAMS IN OT&E PLANNING, EXECUTION, ANALYSIS, AND REPORTING. IN SUPPORT OF CYBERSECURITY AND CYBER SURVIVABILITY TEST AND EVALUATION (T&E), THE OEC ALSO PROVIDES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO THE JITC CYBER SURVIVABILITY ASSESSMENT TEAM (CSAT). ALSO, THE OEC PROVIDES TECHNICAL SUPPORT TO OTHER JITC T&E SERVICE AREAS AND PROCESSES SUCH AS THE JITC TEST AND EVALUATION SCORECARD AND THE APPLICATION OF SCIENCE BASED TEST DESIGN (SBTD) METHODS.

subaward_description: THIS TO WILL ENSURE THE JITC DRSN PROVIDES INTEROPERABILITY TESTING SUPPORT AND EXECUTION FOR ALL DRSN RELATED HW AND SW PRIOR TO FIELDING INTO THE OPERATIONAL DRSN. TESTING USING THE DRSN TEST PLAN WILL DETERMINE IF THE SYSTEM(S) UNDER TEST (SUT) IS/ARE INTEROPERABLE WITH FIELDED SYSTEMS. TESTING VERIFIES WHETHER THE SUT CORRECTS ANOMALIES EXPERIENCED WITH HW OR SW PREVIOUSLY TESTED OR WITHIN THE OPERATIONAL ENVIRONMENT, AND WHETHER NEW FEATURES AND FUNCTIONS ARE INTEROPERABLE.

subaward_description: THIS CONTRACT WILL PROVIDE TECHNICAL SUPPORT TO DSO FOR THE FOLLOWING TASKS: A. E3 AND SPECTRUM ENGINEERING  ANALYZING EQUIPMENT AND SYSTEMS FOR POTENTIAL E3 PROBLEMS AND RECOMMENDING SOLUTIONS; PERFORMING RADIO FREQUENCY (RF) MEASUREMENTS; ASSISTING THE ACQUISITION COMMUNITY BY ASSESSING E3; DETERMINING AND EVALUATING OPERATIONAL FREQUENCY BANDS; AND PROVIDING ASSISTANCE IN ACQUIRING HOST NATION (HN) APPROVAL FOR EQUIPMENT OPERATION. THE GOVERNMENT MAY REQUIRE SURGE SUPPORT DURING THE BASE OR ANY OPTION PERIOD, AND SURGE MODIFICATIONS WILL BE WITHIN THE SCOPE OF THE CONTRACT AND PROVIDE INCREASED SUPPORT FOR THE DEFINED TASK AREAS OF THIS PWS.
